description.narrative: Support for the implementation of the National Strategy for the Reduction of Adolescent Pregnancy and Child Marriage has resulted in the development of a three-year implementation framework and a monitoring and evaluation plan to address child marriage. Formative research on social behavioural drivers for child marriage was commenced to inform development of social norms programming and to enhance Communication for Development programming and measurement on Social Norms, that will improve the ability of communities and households to promote positive social norms and prevent violence, exploitation and abuse against girls and boys. | Status:Met | As-of Date:05/02/2020
